//CREATE
to create a new React project using Vite, follow these steps:
1. Make sure you have Node.js installed on your machine. You can download it from https://nodejs.org/.
2. Open your terminal or command prompt.
3. Run the following command to create a new React project using Vite:
  npm create vite@latest my-react-app -- --template react -> This command will create a new directory called "my-react-app" with the React template set up.
4. Navigate into the project directory:
cd my-react-app
5. Install the project dependencies by running:
npm install

//RUN
To run it the server, use the following command:

cd my-react-app -> to change directory to the project folder
                    but if its already done, skip this step.

Then run:

npm run dev -> to start the development server
You should see output similar to this:

  VITE v4.0.0  ready in 300 ms

  ➜  Local:   http://localhost:3000/
  ➜  Network: use --host to expose


//Shortcuts
  press r + enter to restart the server
  press u + enter to show server url
  press o + enter to open in browser
  press c + enter to clear console
  press q + enter to quit